	<main>
		<img width="2500" height="1201" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="Karen fisher catching shrimp" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay-1536x738.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay-2048x984.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-ngapi-photo-essay-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">When Karen families from Myanmar migrated to India’s Andaman Islands, they brought their tradition of fermenting shrimp along with them. Photo by Sumer Rao</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">The Salty, Sun-Dried Shrimp Paste That Tastes Like Home</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">A fermented seafood delicacy keeps the Karen people of India connected to their homeland in Myanmar.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						Story and photographs by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/sumer-rao/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Sumer Rao</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						October 10, 2024 | 2,100 words, 11 photos
					</aside>

					
